Package: test-inline-pm
Version: 0.15
Revision: 1
Depends: test-harness-pm
Source: mirror:cpan:authors/id/M/MS/MSCHWERN/Test-Inline-%v.tar.gz
Type: perl
UpdatePOD: true
CompileScript: <<
  perl Makefile.PL LIB=%p/lib/perl5 -n PREFIX=%p INSTALLPRIVLIB=%p/lib/perl5 INSTALLARCHLIB=%p/lib/perl5/darwin INSTALLSITELIB=%p/lib/perl5 INSTALLSITEARCH=%p/lib/perl5/darwin INSTALLMAN1DIR=%p/share/man/man1 INSTALLMAN3DIR=%p/share/man/man3
  make
<<
DocFiles: Changes MANIFEST*
Description: Inlining your tests next to the code being tested
DescDetail: <<
Embedding tests allows tests to be placed near the code its testing.
This is a nice supplement to the traditional .t files.  It's like
XUnit, Perl-style.
<<
